-- Paradis Says He’s Confident Canada Can Have 4th Mobile Provider
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2013-06-19T17:22:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-19/paradis-says-he-s-confident-canada-can-have-4th-mobile-provider.html
Canadian Industry Minister Christian
Paradis said he’s confident the country can have a fourth
wireless carrier to bolster competition.  Paradis, speaking to reporters in Ottawa today, declined to
comment on Orascom Telecom Holding SAE’s announcement today that
its dropping its request for regulatory approval to acquire Wind
Mobile, the largest of three recently created wireless operators
based in Ontario.  “I’m confident we can have a fourth player,” Paradis
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theophilos Argitis in Ottawa at 
